{{Infobox Christian leader | type = Bishop | name = Carlos González Cruchaga | title = [[Bishop]] of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Talca|Diocese of Talca]] (Emeritus) | image = | alt = | caption = | church = [[Roman Catholic Church]] | archdiocese = | diocese = | see = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Talca|Diocese of Talca]] | term = 1967–1996 | predecessor = Manuel Larraín Errazuriz | successor = Horacio del Carmen Valenzuela Abarca <!-- Orders --> | ordination = September 23, 1944 | ordinated_by = | consecration = | consecrated_by = | rank = <!-- Personal details --> | birth_date = {{Birth date |1921|6|8}} | birth_place = [[Santiago, Chile]] [[Image:Flag of Chile.svg|25px]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2008|9|21|1921|6|8}} | death_place = [[Santiago, Chile]] | previous_post = Priest }}
'''Carlos González Cruchaga''' (born June 8, 1921 in [[Santiago, Chile]] &ndash; died September 21, 2008) was a [[Chile]]an [[Bishop (Catholic Church)|Bishop]] of the [[Roman Catholic Church]].
Cruchaga was ordained a priest on September 23, 1944. He was appointed bishop of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Talca|Diocese of Talca]] on January 4, 1967 and ordained a bishop May 7, 1967. Cruchaga remained bishop of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Talca|Diocese of Talca]] until his retirement on December 12, 1996.
