{{Infobox Christian denomination |name = Dutch Reformed Church in Botswana |main_classification = [[Protestant]] |theology = [[Reformed]] |polity = [[Presbyterian]] |founded_date = 1863 |founded_place = [[Botswana]] |associations = [[World Communion of Reformed Churches]] |congregations = 13 and 50 house fellowships |members = 6,000 }}
The '''Dutch Reformed Church in Botswana''' was founded by [[Swiss]] missionaries led by Rev. Henri Gronin begun working in 1863 among the tribe [[Bakgatla]], [[Kgafela]] in [[Saulsport]] and [[Rustenburg]] in [[South Africa]]. In 1870 part of the tribe moved north to [[Botswana]] and the missionaries followed them. The great chief was baptised and most of the tribe followed him. In 1966 when Botswana become independent, a Synod of the Reformed Church was formed. In the 1970s the church gained independence. The church in the following years expanded to [[Basarwa]], [[Bakalanga]] and [[Bakgatla]].<ref name="reformiert-online1">{{cite web|author=Johannes a Lasco Library |url=http://www.reformiert-online.net/adressen/detail.php?id=1271&lg=eng |title=Address data base of Reformed churches and institutions |publisher=Reformiert-online.net |date= |accessdate=2013-08-18}}</ref>
The denomination has 6,000 members and 13 parishes with 50 house fellowships in 2 presbyteries and one Synod. The 14 churches are in : [[Muchudi]], Muchudi East, Muchudi West, [[Sikwane]], [[Gaborone]], [[Tlokweng]], [[Lobatse]], [[Kgalagadi District|Kgalagadi]], [[Ghanzi]], [[Maun, Botswana|Maun]], [[Makaleng]], [[Selebi Phikwe]], [[Boseja (Mochudi)]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.localbotswana.com/company/9986/DUTCH_REFORMED_CHURCH_IN_BOTSWANA_SYNOD_OFFICE |title=Dutch Reformed Church In Botswana (Synod Office) (Mochudi, Botswana) |publisher=Localbotswana.com |date=2013-08-06 |accessdate=2013-08-18}}</ref>
The church subscribe the Reformed confessions: *[[Apostles Creed]] *[[Nicene Creed]] *[[Canons of Dort]] *[[Heidelberg Catechism]].<ref name="reformiert-online1"/>
The church is member of the [[World Communion of Reformed Churches]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.wcrc.ch |title=World Communion of Reformed Churches - WCRC &#124; Bringing together 80 million Reformed Christians worldwide |publisher=Wcrc.ch |date= |accessdate=2013-08-18}}</ref>
