'''Franklin Ruehl''' was an [[United States|American]] actor,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1432981/|title=Franklin Ruehl|publisher=imdb.com|accessdate=2016-07-31}}</ref> [[ufologist]] and [[cryptozoologist]].{{Citation needed|date=July 2016}} He has appeared on such shows as ''[[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]]'', ''[[The Roseanne Show]]'' and ''[[Tom Green Live]]'' among others. Ruehl's own show, ''Mysteries from Beyond the Other Dominion'',<ref>{{cite press release |last=Cruz |first=Nancy |date=2014-10-31|title=Our Fascination With Zombies Featuring Dr. Franklin Ruehl, Ph.D. |url=http://ktla.com/2014/10/31/our-fascination-with-zombies-featuring-dr-franklin-ruehl-ph-d/ |location=[[Los Angeles]] |publisher=ktla.com |agency=[[KTLA]] |access-date=2016-07-31}}</ref> started on a [[public-access television]] [[cable TV]] channel in the Los Angeles area in the late 1980s, and then became the first [[Syfy|Sci Fi Channel]]  original series in 1992. In 2006, he hosted several new episodes of the show on [[Tom Green's House Tonight#The Channel|TomGreen.com]].

Ruehl was rejected on an ''[[America's Got Talent]]'' audition with an act that encompassed sticking straws into a potato. In 2010, he appeared on several episodes of ''[[1000 Ways to Die]]'', as an expert, portraying a cryptozoologist, a [[Conspiracy theory|conspiracy]] expert and a deathologist/[[thanatologist]]. His show ''[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2348854/ Professor Weird]'' debuted at 9pm on August 18, 2012 on the [[Science Channel]].

Ruehl has been a regular on "A Current Affair" (2005), "9 On The Town" (with a UFO segment), "Strange Universe," "[[Weird TV]]," and ''[[Ancient Aliens]]'' (on the History Channel).  He co-hosted a radio program on [[Blog Talk Radio]], "Hypergalactic Enigmas." Ruehl has a series of videos entitled ''The Realm of Bizarre News'', which can be viewed [https://web.archive.org/web/20080725103902/http://www.videojug.com/user/dr%20ruehl/ here].

He held a [[Doctor of Philosophy|Ph.D.]] in theoretical [[nuclear physics]] from [[University of California, Los Angeles|UCLA]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/author/dr-franklin-ruehl-phd|title=Dr. Franklin Ruehl, Ph.D. |publisher=[[The Huffington Post]]|accessdate=24 December 2016}}</ref>

Ruehl died in November 2015, of natural causes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sidelongglancesofapigeonkicker.blogspot.ca/2016/05/rip-dr-franklin-ruehl.html|title=RIP, Dr. Franklin Ruehl|date=May 12, 2016|publisher=Sidelong Glances of a Pigeon Kicker|accessdate=24 December 2016}}</ref>

