'''Trilok Teerth Dham''' is a Jain temple in [[Bada Gaon]], [[Baghpat]], [[Uttar Pradesh]].

==Location==
Trilok Teerth Dham is situated in [[Khekra]] in "Parshvanatha Atishaya Kshetra", [[Bada Gaon]], [[Uttar Pradesh]].<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.amarujala.com/uttar-pradesh/baghpat/the-team-then-went-to-the-ministry-of-tourism-dham-pilgrimage |title=पर्यटन मंत्रालय की टीम फिर पहुंची तीर्थ धाम |work=[[Amar Ujala]] |date=6 August 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{citation |url=http://www.amarujala.com/uttar-pradesh/baghpat/the-team-surveyed-tourists |title=टीम ने पर्यटक स्थल का सर्वे किया |work=[[Amar Ujala]] |date=5 August 2016 }}</ref>

==Architecture==
Trilok Teerth Dham is built in shape of Jain Emblem. This temple is 317 feet in height out of which 100 feet is below the ground and 217 feet above the ground.<ref name="jainsamaj">{{cite web|url=http://www.jainsamaj.org/rpg_site/literature2.php?id=3950&subcat=123&subsubcat=44|publisher=jainsamaj.org|title=on www.jainsamaj.org ( Jainism, Ahimsa News, Religion, Non-Violence, Culture, Vegetarianism, Meditation, India. )|accessdate=20 August 2016}}</ref> On top of the temple there is a 31 feet tall statue of Rishabhdev made up of ''[[Ashtadhatu]]'' (8 metals) in padmasan posture. This temple is dedicated to Parshvantha. This temple also has a 108 feet ''Manasthamb'' (tower of pride). The main idol was found in 1922 when Jain saint Anant Kirti Maharaj predicted that the idol was in the hill. As the name suggests trilok teerth depicts the three lokas i.e. Adholok Madhyalok and Urdhvalok.<ref name="jainteerth">{{cite web|url=http://jainteerth.com/uttar-pradesh-u-p-jain-teerth/trilok-teerthdham-badagaon/|publisher=jainteerth.com|title=Trilok Teerthdham Atishay Kshetra Badagaon &#8211; JainTeerth.com|accessdate=20 August 2016}}</ref> 

This temple includes a meditation center, Samavasarana, Nandishwar Dweep, Trikaal Chaubisi, Meru Temple, Lotus Temple, Parshvanath temple, Jambudweep. The temple also has a dharamshala equipped with all modern facilities.<ref name="jaintirthyatra">{{cite web|url=http://www.jaintirthyatra.com/Tirth-Details/1507/.aspx|publisher=jaintirthyatra.com|title=Trilok Teerth Dham,Badagaon Uttar Pradesh|accessdate=20 August 2016}}</ref><ref name="trilokteerthdham">{{cite web|url=http://www.trilokteerthdham.com/about-trilokteerth-2/|publisher=trilokteerthdham.com|title=Trilokteerthdham &raquo; About Trilokteerth|accessdate=20 August 2016}}</ref>

